description: Another exciting adventure in the Punch Drunk saga!
name: Paid In Full

description: Hector is out of the jungles and into the city, caught between warring factions and forced to do the unthinkable: sacrifice a human being! With death, disaster, and darkness on the horizon, how far will Hector go to save the Aztec Empire! Join Hector, a dude on a one-way trip through the past, the present, and the psychedelic into the the glory of the Aztec Empire in SACRIFICE -- a new comic book by SAM HUMPHRIES (writer of ULTIMATES, UNCANNY X-FORCE, OUR LOVE IS REAL and rising star DALTON ROSE.
name: Death, Disaster, and Darkness

description: Coleman stumbles onto the set of "Entourage" in LA, Fairbanks gets revenge for Steve Irwin, Sawyer's romance with Delilah Wilson heats up, and Cecania begins acting disturbingly out of character! SEXY BONUS: Each issue includes a peek into Cecania's Private Party, the fan-service-fueled SORE THUMBS subscription site!
The second exciting issue of Strange Attractors!

A girl named Penny and her dog, Bolt, are the stars of a TV series called "Bolt." To make the series more realistic, the producers stage a fake kidnapping of Penny, but when Bolt thinks it is real, he decides to go look for her! Convinced he has super powers, Bolt starts his journey in search of Penny, a journey that takes him to New York, Hollywood, and Las Vegas, where he meets new friends and faces untold adventures!

Lighting McQueen is back in Radiator Springs, where he is challenged by an Italian car, Francesco Bernoulli, to compete in the World Grand Prix to determine the fastest car! Lighting accepts the challenge and embarks, together with his friend Mater, in a journey through Europe and Japan! While Lighting is busy trying to win the World Grand Prix, Mater is hired by an international espionage association, which will force him to decide whether to support his friend or help with the top-secret mission?

Fans of classic cartoons will love this new series by animators Gene McGuckin (Ren and Stimpy, Foster's Home For Imaginary Friends) and Frank Forte (Bob's Burgers, The Super Hero Squad Show). This delightfully animated comic introduces the large, drunken, obnoxius Cletus and, his brother, the skinny, stuttering, twitching Floyd. The crazed Cletus is constantly beating on the lanky Floyd, but eventually Floyd gets his revenge. The series will cronicle their adventures "Down On The Farm" and beyond. In "Gone Fishin'", Floyd is attempting to catch a goldfish in a goldfish bowl, but the insane Cletus takes over and shows him how it's done. The Cletus and Floyd show is a twisted cross between Laurel and Hardy, Ren and Stimpy and Foghorn Leghorn. PLUS-- special gallery section featuring concept art, character design and animation tests.

An epic re-imagining of Shotaro Ishinomori's manga classic CYBORG 009, CYBORG 009: CHAPTER 000 is the historic first chapter of the forthcoming Archaia graphic novel coming this summer. Cyborg 009: Chapter 000 features the first ever truly digital variant cover created exclusively for comiXology using it's Guided View technology. (PLEASE ENABLE GUIDED VIEW BEFORE READING!) When a young man known only by the numerical designation "009" discovers that his body has been cybernetically augmented and "improved" against his will, he must break free from the clutches of The Black Ghost, a secret society hell-bent turning humans into cybernetic weapons of mass destruction for sale to the highest bidder. Written by F.J. DeSanto (The Spirit, Insurgent) and Bradley Cramp (Gattaca, Lord of War) and stunningly illustrated by Marcus To (Batwing, Huntress, Red Robin) and Ian Herring (Jim Henson's Tale of Sand), Archaia and Ishimori Productions are proud to present this incredible new take on one of the most famous manga titles of all time!
name: Chapter 000

description: Imagine a story that you can drink, a story that you can feel, a story you can live. Welcome to the city of Dante, and the world of Memetech. As a wave of drugs that create living stories sweeps his city, one man fights back as 'The Dark'. A vigilante who wields fiction as a weapon, he is the last hope for a city where nothing is what it seems. A stunning new sci-fi thriller.
name: TPB

description: The warrior Denali embarks on a quest across a post-apocalyptic world, aided by a magician/thief named Paris a yeti named Grok.

After crash-landing on a distant planet, which leaves everyone onboard dead, Chromatic, a member of an elite superhero team, is reassembled and resurrected by the indigenous aliens utilizing the usable body parts of his teammates and enemy. As Chromatic deals with the loss of his colleagues as well as his own identity, he must also come to terms with not just who he is, but what he is.
name: GN

description: This tie-in comic to the all-new game universe, takes place before DmC Devil May Cry and reveals the unmissable backstory of Dante's twin brother Vergil and the mysterious Kat! This digital-first release is exclusive to comiXology!

volume.name: DmC Devil May Cry: The Chronicles of Vergil

description: Donald and the nephews are space traders! So the voyage home should be a breeze? right? After all, Donald is an expert traveler and has the space map in his head! plus: Local wizard Donald Duck just wants to be left alone. But that's not easy when you have a magical crystal ball that allows other s to contact you! This time it's a Landlord under siege from a ferocious dragon. Unfortunately, Wizard Donald just isn't interested. No matter what the landlord says, nothing seems to get Donald excited about this mission. Well, almost nothing! and: Donald Duck and Gus Goose are on an interplanetary mission, in search of rare materials to bring back to Earth! But on the planet they discover, it seems that the only richness is in the food! Gus Goose is enthusiastic, but not Donald Duck. What should they do?

volume.name: Ducks in Space: Voyage Home/Donald Duck and the Dragon of the Eastern Valley/Donald Duck and the Out-Of-This-World Diet

description: You knock at the door of the old mansion up on the hill, and who answers? Your host, none other than Gene Simmons, beckoning you inside. The door slams shut. You try to run, but it's too late... you've entered the home of Simmons Comics Group and there's no turning back! Gene Simmons House of Horrors includes the fifteen different and terrifying stories all presided over by Simmons and featuring a cover by fellow legend Todd McFarlane!

International superstar Gene Simmons creates his own version of the classic 'stranger in a strange land' in this first collection of his all-new science fiction title, Zipper. After a daring escape from his other-dimensional home, the Nether Ether, denizen Xeng Ral finds himself on planet Earth--lost, alone, curious and confused. Protected only by a specially equipped exo-suit, Xeng Ral sets out to explore his new world, finding both allies and enemies, all the while desperately evading those who would hunt him down from the Nether Ether.
name: GN

description: It's the long awaited day of the GlobWorld tournament and all of your favorite Globs are here. Prepare for the epic battle to see who is the strongest, fastest, and cleverest of all the Globs. No matter who wins, with GlobWorld it's a guarantee that everyone will have fun.

In the 1950s, the U.S. Navy encountered and destroyed a gigantic octopus that attacked shipping and wreaked havoc on the west coast of the United States. American forces killed the creature and ended the threat once and for all. Or so they thought. They were wrong. Now, another monster is rising in the warm blue waters surrounding Taru Taru, a speck of land far out in the Pacific. And this time it?s worse than anyone ever imagined.
name: GN

volume.name: It Came From Beneath The Sea... Again!

description: No army has ever marched into battle thinking they were the bad guys. And it's up to the reader to decide who is the hero... and who is the villain?
name: GN

description: The quiet life of a Chinese village is shaken by the unexpected arrival of the Huns, who managed to cross the Great Wall! By order of the Emperor, one man from each family has to join the army. Mulan, a girl from the Fa family, decides to disguise herself as a man and join up to save her elderly father from serving. By her side is a funny little dragon ready to help...

The incredible imagination that brought you AUGUST MOON is back with another wild adventure! Diana Thung welcomes you to Botany, a quaint and quiet little town nestled in the wintry hills. Here, Oliver Peach had a life of simple pleasures -- making puppets, working in his dad's tailor shop, and rockin' out to the music of his friends' band, the Beebop Beans. But when he accidentally thaws out a long-extinct critter frozen in a ball of ice, wild things start happening everywhere! Suddenly the kids are overrun by strange animal migrations, mysterious music, and ghost sightings? and the grownups in town are really starting to lose it. Can Oliver, the Beans, and the ever-inquisitive Tippi Strawberry get to the bottom of this mystery -- and still play the greatest show of their lives at the Splendour in the Snow festival? Dive in and find out! This full-length tome reads like a delicious slushy blend of South Park, Scott Pilgrim, and Spiral-Bound, with that special touch of Diana Thung charm -- a heartwarming adventure for a cold wintry day.
name: GN

description: Tooth and Nail is a parody webcomic that has been adapted in full issue form (bi-annual releases) for Alterna Comics' digital lineup. Inside this book you'll find all sorts of commentaries and lampooning of pop culture-- from film, comics, cartoons, politics, and more. It pleases, teases, and might just spread diseases. You'll laugh, you'll cry, and you'll obviously try to adopt a chimp. Unfortunately, we can't promise you'll pass the screening process. It's pretty damn thorough.
A mysterious kidnapping, and a father's doubt -ridden race against time to save his child and face down a debt that cannot be repaid.
FREE 91-PAGE GIANT! Get to know the heroes of the WAYWARD SONS universe in this handy handbook spotlighting the Ulympeans. And did we mention it's FREE?

volume.name: Wayward Sons: Legends Handbook - Ulympean Special

description:
When Calie left the Liddle home she had no idea of the terrible legacy she was leaving behind. A house possessed by the evil of Wonderland it has been taking victims for years and years. Some innocent, and some not so innocent. Now the story of the house of madness is collected here for the first time ever. If walls could speak, these would scream.

Note: The cover is a homage to a famous scene in the movie "Shining"!
name: TPB

person_credits.name: Jim Davis
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: Prognostications for 2013! CBG #1699 looks at what's coming from several publishers in the new year! Plus, commentary and reviews you can't find anywhere else.
name: Vol. 43 #3

person_credits.name: Will Eisner
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: Issue is numbered PMB
name: Popeye meets Bigfoot

description: Clueless, nave, full of dreams - and unemployed. Fresh out of art school, Dino is ready to start a new chapter in his life, but can't figure out how, and struggles to find his identity as an artist. With a little encouragement from a classmate, he sets out on a fantastic inner journey to wipe the dust off his teenage obsessions and reignite his passion. Blending fact and fiction, past and present, pencil and paint, debut author Dino Pai brings a wide range of voices and influences to bear on the most intimate story in his heart, in this Xeric Award-winning graphic novel.
name: GN

description: From Stephen L. Stern, writer of Markosias masterful Beowulf Graphic Novel, and acclaimed artist Douglas A. Sirois, comes this superb full-color adaptation of Dickens timeless classic. Sacrificing none of Dickens rich language and filled with cinematic artwork, A Christmas Carol is a wonderfully faithful adaptation of the quintessential Christmas story.
name: GN

description:
Sean Andersons greatest concern right now is surviving 10th grade. He has no idea that a series of events which began on a Virginia plantation in 1690, will lead him to gain the absolute power to set a fractured world on the right course.

That is, if he can survive 1st period.

It was on a crisp October morning in 1965 when Snoopy saluted his ground crew, hopped aboard his trusty Sopwith Camel, and took to the skies as the dashing and daring World War I Flying Ace ever on the hunt for the elusive Red Baron! Discover the origins of Snoopys most famous alter-ego in the first of a four part collection of the complete Flying Ace Adventures! The 1960s Part 1 of 4, BW 110 strips
name: Part 1 of 4: 1960-1969

description: The economy is crumbling like stale roquefort. We are at war with Owl Kaida, our soldiers being targeted by their traps, poisons and predators. When the nation, perhaps the whole world, needs change, one rodent steps forward to offer it: Barack Obamouse. But if his daring plans for the country are to succeed, he will have to win over his skeptic political rivals and countrymice, including Hen Beck, John McCrane, Sarah Penguin and Ratt Limbaugh!

The Peebos, Brianna Diggers' super-smart bit-bombs, are back in FULL COLOR! Enjoy Advanced A.I. antics old and new as these mini-marvels discover video games, guilt, manners, fine(?) art, role-playing and much more! These little powder kegs will have you exploding-with laughter! This time, Peebri discovers a brand new video game, all about rolling up big balls of stuff, and she can't get enough of it! And Gina's lab may hold the key to enjoying the game in a whole new way....

volume.name: Gold Digger: Peebo Tales Summer Fun Special

description: Upon her return to Kansas, Dorothy has some explaining to do! After a tearful reunion with her Aunt Em and Uncle Henry, Dorothy recounts her adventures in the magical land of Oz. She details the quest for Glenda the Good Witch of the South, the solution to the curse of the winged monkeys, and the Cowardly Lion's ascent to being the King of Beasts!

Rod Espinosa, A.P.'s Eisner-nominated master storyteller, brings another classic tale to life with his own incredible artistic spin! From the creator of Courageous Princess, Neotopia, and Prince of Heroes comes this unique, gorgeously illustrated take on Charles Dickens' tale of Yuletide redemption for the miserly Scrooge! Let the spirit(s) move you this holiday season!

The secrets of the DinoWars are revealed! Follow the creation and evolution of this groundbreaking series! Acclaimed creator Rod Espinosa provides sauropod-sized portions of background research character notes and sketches, creature statistics, three-dimensional models, and much more!

Special Halloween edition! Gather around the campfire for the monster mayhem as "Grandpa" Harkes Warlock tells the tale of his first spine-tingling adventure and how the legend of Halloween truly began! Learn how he managed to face the Headless Horseman without losing his head! Then enjoy a bonus "IHM mini" adventure as Will and the gang take you trick-or-treating with a pack of mischievous space gremlins!

volume.name: Tales of Sleepy Hollow: The Lost Chronicles of I Hunt Monsters

description: Anrack and his fighters - Naga, Hirotsu, Kyoko, Sakuya, and the reluctant warrior Stone continue to dismantle Eon's forces. The tide of battle turns for the worse when Eon decides to end the conflict himself. Death, life, victory... all will be judged by the Chaos Blade!

Eon's search for the key to ultimate power begins in the heart of a Dragon. After shattering the resistance of his superhuman foes, Eon needs only the power of the First Sword, the original Dragon Arm, to force the world to surrender to his will.

Naga, Anrack, and Hirotsu hunt desperately for the First Sword, hoping to thwart Eon's final bid for world domination. The combined might of three armies stands in his way how far is the godlike, terrible Eon willing to go to assure victory, and will mortal courage and steel may be enough to stop him this time.

Naga and Stone covet the First Sword, and now they must face each other and the weight of Eon and his majin army for possession of the ancient blade. Now, Naga must confront her own shadowed soul and her ultimate destiny.
The true power of the First Sword is unleashed, and the world is about to change forever. Naga and Eon begin an earth-shattering confrontation that may claim creation itself!

The Ultimate Manga Fantasy-Epic comes to an unrelenting climax. In the wake of the final battle between Eon and Naga, only time can judge victory and human cost against a bitter speculation: Is the war over, or has it merely begun?

Will Warlock and his mighty Monster Hunter crew find trouble no matter where they go! Will's dying for date-time with Tayesha, his college classmate and one of the three fine femmes on his team. But the Vampire Lord's hordes are tearing loose in Hong Kong, and it's up to Will's group to shut down this Fang Tong. Can they save a kidnapped Aarna and still stake down the bloodsuckers without her magic? Perfecting jumping-on point for new readers of A.P.'s fastest-rising series!

Will and his team have made their way through the mean streets of Hong Kong to the meaner halls of the Vampire Lord's lair. The fight wears Will down, though, and he finds he must make a drastic sacrifice or have his team fall into the Fang Tong's grasp!

The final showdown between Will and Prince Wei Huang of the Fang Tong! To counter his enemy's supernatural martial arts prowess, Will summons the spirit of a samurai ancestor, channeling his forebear's skills through himself. But will this be enough to bring down the vampire ganglord of Hong Kong?

The Fang Tong has been crippled, but their leader, Wei Huang, has had Delilah kidnapped, and his legal connections mean Will and company can't touch him! But Will's still determined to save Delilah, and gets his amulet to locate her. It guides them to Egypt, where they must face the minions of the Queen of the Undead!

Will and company reach Egypt to rescue the controlled Delilah. They find her, dejected and once more cast out from the vampires, too ashamed to return to her friends. But when the Hunters face the Queen of the Undead's powerful minions, Delilah must act to save them and her self-respect!

Monster-hunting's hard and hungry work, so Will and Aarna head to the grocery store to stock up. But nothing in the monster-hunters' lives is mundane. A gaggle of ghastly gremlins is out to make a cereal killing in the breakfast foods aisle!

Legends tell of a mystic warrior, Volkh, conceived by a woman impregnated by a dragon, who grew up to kill an invading king and marry the queen. Will and the gang go toe-to-toe with this ancient bad@$$ who guards pieces of the coveted enchanted silver cross of Van Helsing.

Will, Aarna and Tayesha head for the recently discovered legendary isle of Avalon, hoping to find Merlin's scrolls. However a horrid creature called the Bookwyrm is eating the magic of the scrolls, and banishes them to a monstrous island!

Exiled on a mystical island, the gang face off against a cadre of strange and impossible creatures. The Prince of Skulls, a foe risen from the ashes of Aarna's past, now holds the fate of the monster hunters in his twisted claws.

Fifteen years from now, the latest virtual addiction is the fighting game Black Wave. Using cell phones, players link minds to do battle in the game. A deranged fan is stalking and killing the game's champions. As the players use the game to track him down, it becomes increasingly difficult to discern the game from reality.

The neural video game Black Wave is the most popular fighting game in the world, and has made Marcus Carter and his friends into millionaires. Now, an obsessed fan is killing them one by one and it's up to Carter to stop the fan from claiming his next victim!

The remaining players of Black Wave regroup in the subway in an effort to find more clues about their stalker. As the search continues, they begin to question the role of the military detectives, Chen and Johnson. Is the military trying to stop the killer, or cover his tracks?

It's a race against time as Chen and Jones fight to save the killer's final target. Even as the military police finally close in, they have no idea that the murderous game they've been playing has only truly just begun. Who will be the final victor in this brutal game of winner takes all?

In the near future, Black Wave is the ultimate in interactive gaming. Its champion players are admired and celebrated. Now they are under attack by the "Ghost," a mystery murderer who might be player or program. The only thing they know for sure is that people are playing - and people are dying.
name: TPB

description: Somewhere in the Caribbean, the armies of post-nuclear Earth gather for a great battle... and after eleven years of war, America will win or lose in this final confrontation! Jed and Toots find themselves in the middle of the last battle of World War Three! The storm gathers...

Marines and U.S. Navy jets wage war against the remaining Nationalist forces occupying a tiny Caribbean island. Rogue Nationalist fighters threaten Marine ground support planes and armor. What price is too high for victory?

Somewhere in the Caribbean, Richard and Melissa discover an island that has become a vast slave labor camp. They must find a way to stop this dictator and free the island. Fortunately, they have help in the form of Neptune, the deadliest, most advanced nuclear submarine on the planet.

Richard and Melissa have discovered a terrible island of death, controlled by the forces of the Neo-Nazis. They must launch an assault to try to free the island people and topple the warlord in charge. They alone must face impossible odds, yet they cannot afford to fail.

Somewhere in the Caribbean, Neo-Nazis and the remnants of the American Navy begin the last battle of World War III. Jed and Toots, aboard the carrier U.S.S. United States, find themselves caught in the middle of Operation Bright Eagle, the last attempt by the Americans to reclaim their homeland.

Old America prepares to launch a massive strike against Nationalists in the Caribbean. A deadly tropical storm threatens the fleet, and Jed must lead a team of Special Forces into the heart of the Nationalist stronghold. The last battle of World War III is about to begin!

A dark storm breaks across the Caribbean, threatening to swallow both Richard and Melissa aboard the supersub Neptune, and their sworn enemies, the murderous Nationalist Klan. The Earth itself has joined the last battle of World War 3, and Nature itself will challenge the machinery of Man with water, thunder, and death!

Caught in the middle of a tropical hurricane, Jed and Toots search in vain for their friends, who are trapped between two mighty armies bent on mutual destruction. But there are forces unknown and powers unseen that will change the equation of war in the Caribbean and determine the fate of Old America forever!

50 Cent's life is as dramatic as any of his songs. Bluewater takes a look at the rapper's life, his feuds and, most importantly, his music. This new comic series has been featured in Rolling Stone, E! Entertainment Television, The New York Times, and thousands more sites.

All the single ladies know that Beyonce is one of the hottest musicians in the world, if not the hottest. From dreaming of singing as a young girl to her days in Destiny's Child to current status as a solo pop superstar, take a look behind the curtain at this stellar musician and person. She might not be a superhero, but judging all the things she's done, you'd be hard pressed not to think she is!

They've transcended their vigilant hip-hop roots and have become a global phenomenon, the likes of which the music world has rarely seen and after their tremendous Grammy win, a young hip-hop-hopeful learns just what it takes to become the best while retracing the defining events in each of the band member's funkadelic lives.

Britney Spears - the most famous superstar of the 21st century.What does it take to reach those heights in the Internet Age? What are the hidden costs when every move makes the headlines? More than an entertainment powerhouse, more than a dancer and musician, Britney Spears is a survivor!

Conan O'Brien: The man, the myth, the legend, nay, he's no myth. He's just legend. A giant in both the comedy fields and real life, Conan O'Brien has been working longer than most of his fans have been alive. He has red hair, nay, strawberry locks, and he's an extraordinary dancer. Wait, this is supposed to be a solicitation text for a comic? Um, buy this comic or else! Conan might do something drastic like shave his beard, and the world cannot deal with him clean-shaven anymore!

High speeds and high stakes have followed Danica Patrick throughout her life, and yet, she's never given up and never given in. Bluewater's best-selling biographical comic series continues, putting the pedal to the medal and racing toward that checkered flag to give you all the background information you could ever want on the racing Sports Illustrated cover girl.

From Christian singer to pop superstar, she's been through it all, seemingly. She's been on the cover of every magazine and newspaper in circulation, she's been featured in countless news articles, she's been married and divorced, and she's performed in front of millions. She's Katy Perry, and this comic will teach you everything there is to know about the California girl.

One of the 2010's top news makers is now a comic book sensation! Tiger Woods is, by far, the most famous golfer of all time. Come and see how his life lead him to be one of the most famous sports stars in the history of the United States and the world. Learn about the man behind all the stories. Go for a hole in one with this comic detailing the life story of this major athlete.
Contains : Generation X (1994) #12-14
Contains : Generation X (1994) #15-16 , Untold Tales Of Spider-Man (1995) #12

The wedding of the century is nearly here! Take an in-depth look behind the curtain at the Prince and his soon to be bride. Kate Middleton and Prince William of Wales, the heir presumptive to the British throne, have become global celebrities, and this issue will show you who these people are, giving you a closer look than those photos can ever show you. Available in a comic book edition and a graphic novel edition with additional pages and artwork on the royal couple.

His vices are legendary. His women are unbelievable. His sanity? Constantly in doubt. And so, it comes as no surprise that Charlie Sheen is currently the most fascinating person on the planet. Sheen's rise from actor of some note to Tiger's Blood advocate will be examined in excruciating detail in Bluewater Comics' Infamous: Charlie Sheen. TMZ, eat your heart out.

As the brains and driving force behind Facebook, Mark Zuckerberg has become the youngest billionaire in the history of the planet. The road to success for both his creation and him personally was not preordained nor was it always a smooth ride. Learn how a young man's frustration with women helped spark an idea that would have him dating Victoria's Secret models and how a socially inept young man wound up creating a company that has revolutionized the way hundreds of millions of people all over the globe socialize with each other.
Contains : Generation X (1994) #17-18 , Untold Tales Of Spider-Man (1995) #13

Rap, R&B and Drake! A heady, thought-provoking mixture from a genius in the making who has it all going on. But behind the talent is the person who is very much the man when it counts. Drake is the star your parents hope you grow up to be. Read all about this superstar's rise to stardom, his dedication to family and the adult way in which he deals with the world.
